Patch Set 7: Code-Review+1

Code-wise I am okay with this change. If set, it will treat 't','true', 'on', 'y', 'yes', or '1' as True. Anything else will be treated as False. If the filter is not set, we do not add it.
I am open to having the strict flag of strutils.bool_from_string set to True and catching a ValueError invalidating filters such as protected=whatever (with the current PS this would be translated to protected=False).

Patch Set 7:

This requires a spec because it impacts the API.  There's one up now: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/451560/

Please look at the spec and provide feedback.  It's basically what you have here plus adding strict=True to your use of the oslo strutils and catching the ValueError appropriately.
